        "title_bottom": "Garage",
        "lede": "<p>Designed by a patient. Built for Bite Mechanics.</p>",
        "body": "<p>What started as one person's search for better answers became a growing collection of art, ideas, and gear for people who believe their health belongs in their own hands.</p>",
        "signoff": "<p>Clock in.<br/>Grab your uniform.<br/>The garage is open.</p>",
        "story_kicker": "// How it started",
        "story_heading": "Built by a patient. For future Bite Mechanics.",
        "story_left": "<p>This didn't start in a boardroom. It started after too many appointments, too many unanswered questions, and one simple realization:</p><p><strong>I got tired of believing someone else knew my body better than I did.</strong></p><p>So I started learning.</p>",
        "story_right": "<p>Every design represents curiosity, personal responsibility, and the belief that nobody will ever care about your body more than you do.</p><p>Bite Mechanic exists to celebrate the people willing to ask better questions, build better habits, and take ownership of their own health.</p>",
        "proc_kicker": "// On the workbench",
        "proc_heading": "How a Bite Mechanic makes the merch",
        "founder_kicker": "// Meet the Bite Mechanic",
        "founder_name": "Hi, I'm Dan.",
        "founder_role": "Designer. Illustrator. Professional doodler.",
        "founder_text": "<p>After years of searching for answers, I stopped waiting for someone else to solve my problems and started learning everything I could about my own body.</p><p>Bite Mechanic is my way of sharing that journey through art, ideas, and products that encourage people to stay curious, think independently, and become the expert on the one body they'll have for life.</p>",
